      "rationale": "The relevance of the selected QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) to the clinical decision context was not formally evaluated against the COU risk level. The team relied on the ASTM F1717 standard specification as implicit justification for QoI selection without conducting a structured relevance assessment per ASME V&V 40 Table 5-1 guidance. Given the modelRiskLevel of 3, a formal QoI relevance assessment linking each QoI to the specific harm pathway (screw fracture leading to revision surgery) was required but not performed."
